"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japanese_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japanese_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The sport, which was born at block parties in the Bronx neighborhood in New York in the 1970s, delivered some unexpected drama too.\", \"from\": 1355, \"to\": 1486, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1405, \"end\": 1410, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Bronx\", \"score\": 0.999999999919055, \"rank\": 7.98373172410268e-11, \"text\": \"Bronx\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Bronx\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Bronx\"}, {\"begin\": 1427, \"end\": 1435, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_City\", \"score\": 0.9999999999990905, \"rank\": 6.898262379019199e-13, \"text\": \"New York\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_City\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_City\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Afghan B-Girl Manizha Talash, a member of the refugee Olympic team, was disqualified after displaying the words \\\"Free Afghan Women\\\" on her cape during pre-qualifiers.\", \"from\": 1488, \"to\": 1654, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1488, \"end\": 1494, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Afghans\", \"score\": 0.9996760621193065, \"rank\": 0.0003240412801739569, \"text\": \"Afghan\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Afghans\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Afghans\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Later in the day, B-Girl Raygun (Rachael Gunn), a 36-year-old Australian university lecturer, stood out for her unique approach to the sport, leading to countless online memes.\", \"from\": 1656, \"to\": 1832, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1689, \"end\": 1696, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rachael_Ray\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.643499735707773e-14, \"text\": \"Rachael\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rachael_Ray\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rachael_Ray\"}, {\"begin\": 1697, \"end\": 1701, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Clan_Gunn\", \"score\": 0.7923420577095426, \"rank\": 0.26184986563386564, \"text\": \"Gunn\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Clan_Gunn\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Clan_Gunn\"}, {\"begin\": 1718, \"end\": 1728, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\", \"score\": 0.9999884272343741, \"rank\": 1.1570362814404115e-05, \"text\": \"Australian\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Gunn took the response - some mocking, some praising - in her stride and was smiling in the stands at Saturday's men's competition while Australia's Chef de Mission Anna Meares hit back at criticism by \\\"trolls and keyboard warriors.\\\"\", \"from\": 1834, \"to\": 2067, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1834, \"end\": 1838, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Clan_Gunn\", \"score\": 0.7923420577095426, \"rank\": 0.26184986563386564, \"text\": \"Gunn\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Clan_Gunn\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Clan_Gunn\"}, {\"begin\": 1971, \"end\": 1980, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"score\": 0.999262548165585, \"rank\": 0.0007087321251542692, \"text\": \"Australia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\"}, {\"begin\": 1983, \"end\": 1998, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Head_of_mission\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Chef de Mission\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Head_of_mission\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Head_of_mission\"}, {\"begin\": 1999, \"end\": 2010, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anna_Meares\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Anna Meares\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anna_Meares\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anna_Meares\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"On Saturday the 16 best male breakers in the world took to the cypher - a stage that looks like a cross between a disco dance floor and a mixed martial arts octagon.\", \"from\": 2069, \"to\": 2234, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"There Canada's B-Boy Phil Wizard (Philip Kim) conjured up a gold medal with a spellbinding performance to defeat popular Frenchman B-Boy Dany Dann (Danis Civil).\", \"from\": 2236, \"to\": 2397, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2242, \"end\": 2248, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada\", \"score\": 0.9954001066201535, \"rank\": 0.002995578955851487, \"text\": \"Canada\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada\"}, {\"begin\": 2270, \"end\": 2280, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Philip_Kim\", \"score\": 0.9999999998622116, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Philip Kim\", \"types\": [\"Q901\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Philip_Kim\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Philip_Kim\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The party was not confined to the venue as music and dancing spilled out in sideshows around the grounds, creating a vibe more akin to a summer music festival than a sporting competition.\", \"from\": 2399, \"to\": 2586, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Breaking was added to the programme for Paris 2024 in an effort to attract a younger and more diverse fanbase to the Olympics.\", \"from\": 2588, \"to\": 2714, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2628, \"end\": 2638, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.387805437547057e-15, \"text\": \"Paris 2024\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"While it will not feature in Los Angeles in 2028, its athletes said they were thrilled to have their moment in the Olympic spotlight.\", \"from\": 2716, \"to\": 2849, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2745, \"end\": 2756, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.324912118709125e-14, \"text\": \"Los Angeles\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I have dedicated my life to this,\\\" said B-Boy Phil Wizard.\", \"from\": 2851, \"to\": 2910, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2892, \"end\": 2897, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Breakdancing\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.5371353293626602e-36, \"text\": \"B-Boy\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Breakdancing\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Breakdancing\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It's an underappreciated sport and I hope today we showed the world how incredible breaking is.\\\"\", \"from\": 2912, \"to\": 3009, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"REUTERS  Hip-hop  Olympics  E-paper  Newsletters  Podcasts  RSS Feed  About Us  Terms & Conditions  Personal Data Protection Notice  Need help?\", \"from\": 3010, \"to\": 3153, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3010, \"end\": 3017, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reuters\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"REUTERS\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reuters\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reuters\"}, {\"begin\": 3070, \"end\": 3078, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/RSS\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"RSS Feed\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/RSS\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/RSS\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Reach us here.\", \"from\": 3154, \"t